to DamienIntroSpotted:
	WaitLineBreak;
	say "     Sneaking your way to this odd figure you saw, you attempt to catch them by surprise as you try to be stealthy about this, moving as quietly as you can around the corner of this alley. You are pretty confident you can get a closer look at them before you have to reveal yourself, but as you do so, you are taken aback when laying eyes on what seems to be a fully human individual. Perhaps you expected something else, given the circumstances, but the way this freezes you in place as you rethink your actions leaves you out in the open, giving enough time for the stranger to spot you. The next thing you see is a crossbow pointed at you as the human turns to you, prompting you to raise your hands in a gesture of peace.";
	say "     'Who are you?' he asks, as he slowly walks towards you, keeping his crossbow ready to shoot. It is clearly a man around his early twenties, judging by the young tone of his voice, though as you get a closer look, you see this is no ordinary young man either. He gives you the feeling of a hardened survivor with a quite athletic frame, wearing a black hoodie, a pair of dark jeans and sneakers, carrying a large backpack on his back and several pouches around his waist, even some smaller ones hanging to his legs with a strap. However, you cannot think of a reason why someone would willingly wander the Red Light District, setting traps and camping in the alleys. Perhaps you could ask him, as long as you can convince him you mean no harm.";
	WaitLineBreak;
	if BodyName of Player is listed in infections of DemonList or FaceName of Player is listed in infections of DemonList: [Damien recognizes player as a demon]
		say "     'Did your [italic type]lordship[roman type] send you to come fetch me all on your own, or something?' You give him a confused look, as you really are not sure what he is talking about. 'Oh, don't tell me you're [italic type]new[roman type]... He really sent in a rookie to deal with me? I feel insulted.' Whatever he is saying, you rush to explain yourself and tell him nobody sent you, that you are just someone passing by. 'Then how do you explain... However you look like? Are you intending to tell me you're not a demon?' Oh. It is then that you realize... You do look quite a bit like a demon. Well, that is easy, right? You just explain to him that you had your appearance change due to the infection and it just so happened to be due to getting too close to demons...";
		say "     'Either you're careless or stupid.' Right, perhaps you should also mention a bit of your background, and that despite all your untimely encounters, you are still holding to your humanity, at least mentally. He only stares back at you in silence for a brief moment, then finally lowers his crossbow. 'If this is really true, then I suppose we'll see. Nothing keeps me from shooting you if you try anything funny.' Starting to get a little impatient at all this suspicion, you argue that if you wanted to hurt him, you would have done so already, mentioning the opportunities you had as you approached him while he was not watching. This seems to click in his mind as he finally drops his guard.";
	else:
		say "     'My, my... And so close to demon territory, aren't we? Don't you know it's quite dangerous to wander aimlessly, all by yourself, through some dingy alleys?' he asks, and you can sense a hint of sarcasm in his voice, almost condescending. However, his expression remains serious, vigilant eyes making sure you do not do any sudden movement. Without much of an option, you tell him the truth, that you happened to come across these traps he set and got curious... 'Curiosity killed the cat, or whatever they say. Though, I suppose I shouldn't shoot someone who's intelligent enough to have a coherent conversation, so... For now, you're fine. But don't try anything funny.' With that said, he lowers his crossbow and lets you stand at ease.";
	WaitLineBreak;
	say "     'Well, you can't judge me for being careful when a complete stranger comes waltzing their way into my camping spot. I've had enough of weird shits, such as demons. But, I guess you did get past my traps... That makes you at least smarter than a good bunch of them. And some other creatures along the way... Frankly, this whole place's a mess.' He then begins to walk away, and you rush to catch up to him.";
	DamienIntroEnding;

