to DamienIntroTrapped:
	WaitLineBreak;
	say "     It seems nobody is coming for you, until a few minutes pass and you see someone coming from deeper in the alleyway. It is a humanoid figure, still hidden by the darkness, and they are carrying what seems to be some sort of crossbow. Not only that, he seems to be chuckling as he closes up the distance. Judging by the voice, you could tell this man is in his early twenties, and does look shockingly like a human. Before you begin to think your eyes are deceiving you, his face becomes quite more visible, and you confirm it. It is a man indeed, and no ordinary one at that. He gives you the feeling of a hardened survivor with a quite athletic frame, wearing a black hoodie, a pair of dark jeans and sneakers, carrying a large backpack on his back and several pouches around his waist, even some smaller ones hanging to his legs with a strap. However, you cannot think of a reason why someone would willingly wander the Red Light District, setting traps and camping in the alleys. Perhaps you could ask him, as long as you can convince him you mean no harm.";
	if BodyName of Player is listed in infections of DemonList or FaceName of Player is listed in infections of DemonList: [Damien recognizes player as a demon]
		say "     'Well, now you don't. Hanging up in the air like that, all helpless and harmless... Almost makes demon shits like you pleasant to look at. For a laugh, at least.' Your precarious situation is nothing to be laughed at, one could think, except him, who seems to be having the time of his life enjoying the sights of a successful trap that happened to catch you. Besides, you just happen to look like one because... Well, perhaps you should not explain why, even though it does not take a genius to realize how one comes to be infected. You realize this does not really help you a lot, and the man keeps his sights on you. 'So you fuck them. Great for you, I guess. Not so great that you're starting to become one of them, and definitely not while you're swinging around tied to a rope. Which is mine.'";
		say "     Impatient, you tell him to stop this nonsense and listen to you, as you again explain that you are not a demon by any means, that you are still in control of your thoughts and actions. You were simply too incompetent to get past his clever contraptions, so much that you ended up being caught in one of them. 'Humility isn't something a demon usually knows... Assuming you're not trying to trick me. That's one point in your favor...' he says, but keeps aiming his crossbow at you for brief moments, before finally lowering it down and dropping his guard. 'Alright, I suppose I can give you a chance. If push comes to shove, I know exactly how to deal with the likes of you, anyway.'";
		WaitLineBreak;
		say "     Not knowing the real dimension of what he just said, you figure it is probably better to have him trust you for now, at least. Once he finishes speaking, the man approaches the contraption that has you trapped and begins to lower you carefully to the ground. Then, he takes a knife from one of his pouches and cuts the rope. 'It'd have been impossible to undo this knot, unfortunately... Guess you're owing me this much rope,' he says, tossing the cut part of the rope to the side before he begins to walk away, prompting you to rush in order to catch up to him.";
