to say DamienTalkScavenge:
	now DamienDoneTalking is true;
	if Resolution of DamienIntro is 2:
		say "     You ask Damien if he would like you to accompany him in some scavenging around the district. Maybe on the way, you can assist the young man by being on the lookout for demons and other hostile roamers, and it is always a sort of bonding activity for the both of you. 'I suppose that's a good way to spend time. Here was I wondering if you'd rather be having tea together,' he responds, ending with a clear tone of sarcasm before he chuckles and begins to walk ahead of you. At least, he does not seem too disinclined to have you around, and for you, having such a resourceful partner will definitely make scavenging a lot easier and effective. Before you go, however, Damien stops by one of the garbage containers and takes what seems to be some additional equipment from inside. 'You never know when we need to shoot something on the way,' he says, as he shows you several more bolts for his crossbow.";
		say "     Daring not to question him nor his choices for stashing his valuables, you wait until he is done. 'There, that should be everything. I hope you can hold yourself. You better.' Observation made, he beckons you to follow him as you both begin to walk. It does cause you to think whether this man just so happens to be really good at this whole survival thing, or if he is simply immensely paranoid. Nonetheless, no one would probably think of looking into trash containers for valuables, so maybe he has the right idea after all. 'I know what you're thinking. Crazy idiot hiding stuff under garbage, bla-bla... Well, I used to have a base for myself. An abandoned warehouse of sorts. Wasn't particularly safe, though, so I had to find ways to stash my supplies in places nobody would look. Call me paranoid, I guess, but I've been around for long enough to know better.'";
		WaitLineBreak;
		say "     His attitude does not really come to much of a surprise, even more knowing very well of the dangers of the city and its surroundings. Perhaps there were enough experiences for Damien to have learned better, and this is his way of dealing with the current times. You cannot judge him for being too careful, as there is no such thing when almost nowhere is safe. 'As for the rest, I simply set a perimeter of traps to ensure nothing comes close. They're nothing too elaborate, I'm sure anyone with half a brain can figure it out. They aren't meant to trigger on anyone who still has some part of their brains intact. Guess there can always be exceptions...' It also takes some cleverness to set up traps like that, so you ask him where he learned to do that. 'Nowhere in specific, I guess being an engineer helps figure out shit like that.'";
		say "     It would make sense, someone used to figure out contraptions or devices would perhaps find it easier to come up with clever ways to put junk and scrap together. 'As for where or how I learned to do all that... I guess it was out of necessity. When you gotta survive and protect yourself, you sorta have this instinct of learning and improving yourself. And ever since...' he pauses there, hesitating to continue for a moment, but eventually lets out a sigh and carries on speaking, 'I've had an issue with the demons before, as you could probably tell. I wasn't on this alone, but they... Changed that. Took him to their side.' You tell him you do not mean to pry, but it does feel like it was an important person for him. 'He was my friend in the middle of an apocalypse. That's already something invaluable by default, if we're not taking into account this is actually a person I cared about. Anyway... Yeah, they deserve to pay for that.'";
		say "     'But let's focus on the task at hand, shall we? I've had enough of sharing my sad life.' While you are conversing, you exit the alley and head into less visited areas, in hopes to find something useful for both of you. Though as you pass through Crimson Street, the man's attention turns towards the Hellfire Club... After a long moment of silence, he turns around and continues walking down the street with you. 'We used to visit the club, it was a nice way to let out some steam, even though I always had a feeling they were up to no good... But the demons there were so nice and welcoming, made us feel comfortable in there... It seems to have been all but a scheme to catch us off guard and get a hold of our souls. They almost fully succeeded...'";
		WaitLineBreak;
		say "     'I immediately feared betrayal the day my friend simply disappeared. He was nowhere to be found, didn't return to our shelter, didn't leave any messages... Nothing. I then went back to the club and asked [bold type]Mogdraz[roman type] directly, and the fucker didn't even try to hide it. He said it to my face that they took his soul and welcomed him into their ranks, by his request...! Yeah, by his request my ass. How the fuck would he...' His voice begins to show more and more anger as he goes on, but gets a hold of himself before it happens. 'They fucking tricked him. They must have put something on his drink, or cast some demonic sorcery on him, I don't fucking know.' The reason to why he hates demons seems clear enough. His friend gave away his soul to the Hellfires, and Damien understands he has been tricked into doing that.";
		say "     'Let's just keep moving. I don't want to linger here.' You then agree to head deeper into the street, about to move into some alleys between a bunch of residential buildings. Damien keeps talking, but lowering his voice as you both walk on ahead. 'I want my message to be clear to them. No one fucks with me, and especially with those I love and care for. Anyway... Sorry for the rant, I guess. I underestimated how fucking miserable it feels to not have anyone to talk to for so long.' These are his final words on the subject before you turn your attention to the urban landscape in front of you. It is nothing impressive, really, just several shattered ground floor windows and the generic desolate street. You are not quite familiar with this area of the district, but you can tell it probably has also been completely ransacked.";
		LineBreak;
		say "     'I usually don't find much around here besides some junk and unused parts for my craftworks. I take it you'd prefer to look for something more edible?' he asks you, looking at you directly as he is about to examine one of the windows.";
		LineBreak;
		say "     ([link]Y[as]y[end link]) - Say that you would prefer looking for edible supplies, indeed.";
		say "     ([link]N[as]n[end link]) - Tell him you are fine with whatever he decides.";
		if Player consents:
			LineBreak;
			say "     You state your preference for trying to find perhaps food or water, and he nods as he hears you. 'Alright, then I suppose we could try...' he stops talking, and at first, you do not really know why. 'Wait, I think I heard something.'";
