			say "     You say nothing and trust Damien's word, even though you fear the consequences of it. Nevertheless, you think you could have not warned them in time, as Damien is quick to take his shot. 'Got it,' he reassures, and almost immediately, you can hear Arad shouting in the distance, holding his demon brother and keeping him from collapsing on the floor. You figured that worked out, at least.";
		WaitLineBreak;
		say "     'Egran! Stop messing around! What the...?!' he then stops, and before Damien can take the second shot, Arad shoots him back with a fireball, which forces you to leap out of position and roll on the ground. Once he realizes who the two of you are, he stops and exclaims, 'It's you?!' The young man at your side keeps his crossbow aimed at Aran as he speaks, 'You try anything else and you're gonna get it too, Arad.' If you had any suspicions before, this confirms that Damien knows these two as well. 'Damien! Hey! That's... Not the friendliest way to start a conversation!' You can see Arad is... Slightly nervous, to say the least, as he holds his unconscious brother. The demon continues, clearly confused with the current situation, 'What's gotten into you?! I thought we were friends!'";
